// Strings in Java

Definition : 
    A String is a sequence of characters. In Java, a String is an object, and it is immutable.

    Syntax :
        String str = "Hello";
        String str = new String("Hello");

    Methods :
        charAt(int index)
        length()
        substring(int start, int end)
        toLowerCase()
        toUpperCase()
        trim()
        concat(String str)
        replace(char oldChar, char newChar)